  "text": "As noticed in [CITATION_1] , a coloring σ of a cograph G may be an hc-coloring w.r.t. some cotree (T, t) but not w.r.t. to another cotree (T , t ) that yields the same cograph. An example is shown in Fig. 1 . First consider G = G1 G2. Since xy ∈ E(G) for all x ∈ V1 and y ∈ V2 we have σ(x) = σ(y), and hence σ(V1) ∩ σ(V2) = ∅. Thus, σ(V ) = σ(V1) ∪ · σ(V2) and therefore,",
